Patch Set 1: I would prefer that you didn't merge this

Could we come up with a test for this?;  It may be hard to verify that every driver actually deleted the data, but could we at least have code the causes every driver to hit the exception?  As it stands it seems that the changes here are not covered in unit tests.

If doing so in unit tests is too hard to get this patch in quickly (which I imagine it may be) than perhaps we can file a bug on that and move on.
Uploaded patch set 2.

Patch Set 2:

Patch Set 4:

Hi markwash, thanks for you input. I have changed code to using your suggestion in PS5.

But one point for me here is that actually I don't want raise any exception from delete call for partial image cleanup in the PS4, like I said the internal exception will be swallowed. And when I using save_and_reraise_exception() then the internal exception could be raised (https://github.com/openstack/glance/blob/master/glance/openstack/common/excutils.py#L50), and this is useless for my this change.
